          <div class="card-content">
            <div class="content has-text-centered">
              <h3 class="title is-4">Carne Asada</h3>
              <p>Description: Tender and flavorful grilled steak, marinated in a zesty blend of citrus and spices. Perfect for tacos, burritos, or as a main dish with rice and beans.</p>
               <div class="recipe-details" style="max-height: 300px; overflow-y: auto;">
          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Ingredients</h4>
          <ul>
             <li>2 pounds flank or skirt steak</li>
        <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>
        <li>1 jalapeño pepper, seeded and minced</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon chili powder</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon paprika</li>
        <li>1/2 cup fresh lime juice</li>
        <li>1/4 cup fresh orange juice</li>
        <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
        <li>Fresh cilantro, for garnish</li>
          </ul>

          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Preparation</h4>
          <ol>
             <li>In a bowl, combine minced garlic, minced jalapeño, ground cumin, chili powder, paprika, fresh lime juice, and fresh orange juice.</li>
        <li>Place the steak in a resealable plastic bag and pour the marinade over it. Seal the bag and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or overnight for best results.</li>
        <li>Preheat your grill or grill pan to high heat. Remove the steak from the marinade and let any excess drip off.</li>
        <li>Season the steak with salt and pepper. Grill for about 4-6 minutes per side for medium-rare, or to your desired level of doneness.</li>
        <li>Remove the steak from the grill and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing it thinly against the grain.</li>
        <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      
        <button class="button is-primary like-button">Add to Favorites</button>
            </div>
          </div>
