              <h3 class="title is-4">Oxtail Stew</h3>
              <p>Description: Hearty and comforting, this stew features oxtail simmered to tender perfection with aromatic vegetables, herbs, and a rich broth. Served over a bed of rice, it is a soul-warming delight.</p>
               <div class="recipe-details" style="max-height: 300px; overflow-y: auto;">
          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Ingredients</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>2 bell peppers, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1 cup broccoli florets</li>
            <li>1/2 cup snap peas</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1-inch piece of ginger, grated</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons oyster sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
          </ul>

          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Preparation</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, combine soy sauce, oyster sauce, grated ginger, and minced garlic. Add the sliced chicken and marinate for at least 30 minutes.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat. Add marinated chicken and stir-fry until cooked through. Remove from pan and set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, add sesame oil and stir-fry the bell peppers, broccoli, and snap peas until crisp-tender.</li>
            <li>Return the cooked chicken to the pan and toss to combine with the vegetables.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot over steamed rice.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
       
